'''Takeda Suga Shrine''' (健田須賀神社, ''Takeda Suga Jinja'') is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Yūki City|ja|結城市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Ibaraki Prefecture|ja|茨城県|12=draft}}, Japan. The shrine was historically ranked as a {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|ja|県社|12=draft}} under the {{ill|Modern System of Ranked Shinto Shrines|ja|近代社格制度|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|12=draft}}. It was formed during the Meiji period through the merger of '''Takeda Shrine''', a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|12=draft}}, and '''Suga Shrine'''. 

The shrine enshrines {{ill|Take Nunokawa Wake no Mikoto|ja|武渟川別|lt=Takenuokawa Wake no Mikoto|12=draft}} (the former deity of Takeda Shrine) and {{ill|Susanoo|ja|スサノオ|lt=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|12=draft}} (the former deity of Suga Shrine).

It is a provincial soja with provincial Soja shrines which enshrine all the kami of a province<ref>https://archive.ph/wip/XtZfZ</ref>

