'''Takeda Suga Shrine''' (健田須賀神社, ''Takeda Suga Jinja'') is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto shrine|qq=}} located in {{ill|Yūki City|ja|結城市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yūki City|qq=}}, {{ill|Ibaraki Prefecture|ja|茨城県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ibaraki Prefecture|qq=}}, Japan. The shrine was historically Ranked as a {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|ja|県社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prefectural Shrine|qq=}} under the {{ill|Modern System of Ranked Shinto Shrines|ja|近代社格制度|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|1=Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Modern System of Ranked Shinto Shrines|13=User:Immanuelle/Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|qq=}}. It was formed during the Meiji period through the merger of '''Takeda Shrine''', a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}}, and '''Suga Shrine'''. 

The shrine enshrines {{ill|Take Nunokawa Wake no Mikoto|ja|武渟川別|lt=Takenuokawa Wake no Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Take Nunokawa Wake no Mikoto|qq=}} (the former deity of Takeda Shrine) and {{ill|Susanoo|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|スサノオ|lt=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=}} (the former deity of Suga Shrine).

It is a provincial soja with provincial Soja shrines which enshrine all the kami of a province<ref>https://archive.ph/wip/XtZfZ</ref>

== History ==
'''Takeda Shrine''' has an but it is said to have been founded by the {{ill|Yūki no Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|結城国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yūki no Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}} lineage of the {{ill|Takeda no Omi|ja|竹田臣|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeda no Omi|qq=}}, who enshrined their ancestor, Takenuokawa Wake no Mikoto. This deity was one of the {{ill|Shidō Shōgun|ja|四道将軍|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shidō Shōgun|qq=}}, a group of four generals dispatched to pacify and develop the eastern provinces. The shrine is recorded in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}} under "Takeda Shrine of Yūki District, Shimōsa Province," making it one of the 11 shrines listed for Shimōsa Province. In 1764 (Hōreki 14), the shrine was relocated to the grounds of {{ill|Jōkoku-ji|ja|乗国寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōkoku-ji|qq=}}, a {{ill|Sōtō Zen|ja|曹洞宗|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sōtō Zen|qq=}} temple that serves as the ancestral temple of the {{ill|Yūki clan|ja|結城氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yūki clan|qq=}}.

'''Suga Shrine''' was established in 1242 (Ninji 3) when the ruling {{ill|Yūki clan|ja|結城氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yūki clan|qq=}} invited the deity from {{ill|Tsushima Shrine|ja|津島神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsushima Shrine|qq=}} in {{ill|Owari Province|ja|尾張国|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Owari Province|qq=}}, naming it '''Tenno-sha''' (天王社). In 1343 (Kōei 2), {{ill|Yūki Naoasa|ja|結城直朝|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yūki Naoasa|qq=}} designated it as one of the '''Yūki Seven Shrines''' (結城七社) and made it the {{ill|Sōja|ja|総社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sōja|qq=}} (main provincial shrine) of {{ill|Yūki District|ja|結城郷|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yūki District|qq=}}. During the {{ill|Shinbutsu Bunri|ja|神仏分離|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinbutsu Bunri|qq=}} reforms in 1868 (Meiji 1), the shrine was renamed '''Suga Shrine'''. 

In 1870 (Meiji 3), Takeda Shrine was separated from Jōkoku-ji and merged with Suga Shrine, forming '''Takeda Suga Shrine'''. In 1873 (Meiji 6), the shrine was designated as a {{ill|Gōsha|ja|郷社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gōsha|qq=}}, and in 1930 (Shōwa 5), it was elevated to a {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|ja|県社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prefectural Shrine|qq=}}.

