'''Takeda Suga Shrine''' (健田須賀神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:Yūki, Ibaraki|Yūki, Ibaraki]], Japan. The shrine is classified as a former Prefectural Shrine and was formed in the Meiji period by merging the {{ill|Takeda Shrine|ja|健田神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeda Shrine|qq=}} and {{ill|Suga Shrine|ja|須賀神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suga Shrine|qq=}}, with the former being a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}}.

The shrine enshrines {{ill|Takenouchi no Sukune|ja|武渟川別命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takenouchi no Sukune|qq=}}, the deity of the original Takeda Shrine, and {{ill|Susanoo|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|須佐之男命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=}}, the deity of the original Suga Shrine.

